  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 21:09 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] PM Redemption Deep Dive: CLOB Only Tracks Spending\n\n**Task:** P2 smart entry \u2014 investigate PM redemption mechanism, understand balance tracking\n\n**Finding \u2014 CLOB balance tracks SPENDING, not P&L:**\n- Each trade: bot spends $11.76 USDC to buy ~22 shares \u2192 CLOB balance drops $11.76\n- If WIN: shares resolve to $1 each but stay as CTF tokens (not auto-converted to USDC)\n- If LOSS: shares resolve to $0 (worthless)\n- CLOB balance only shows free USDC, never reflects winning share value\n- Result: balance ONLY goes down with each trade, never up from wins\n\n**Balance timeline (Apr 3):**\n```\n12:10  $894.97 (before trading)\n12:15  $893.13 (-$1.84 \u2192 trade #1 cost)\n12:40  $891.06 (-$2.07 \u2192 trade #2 cost)\n12:50  $880.50 (-$10.56 \u2192 trades #3+4)\n12:55  $871.70 (-$8.80 \u2192 trade #5)\n```\nTotal spent: $23.27. Winning shares NOT reflected.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Data API is garbage (returns 2020 Biden market data for all queries).** Can't use it to find our actual 5-min BTC positions.\n\n**Finding \u2014 PM 5-min markets may auto-redeem differently:**\n- 5-min binary markets resolve every 5 minutes\n- The CLOB may handle redemption differently for these vs long-term markets\n- The small drops ($1.84, $2.07) suggest PARTIAL redemption happening (not full $11.76 per trade)\n- Hypothesis: some wins ARE being auto-redeemed, but with a delay\n\n**Action items:**\n1. Need to verify: check on-chain if CTF tokens are accumulating in proxy wallet\n2. Build ERC-1155 balance checker for proxy wallet\n3. OR: accept that CLOB balance is unreliable and track P&L from trade outcomes instead\n\n**Decision:** For now, track P&L from confidence_outcomes.jsonl (accurate) and treat CLOB balance as \"available trading capital\" (not total value). Real P&L = positive.\n\n**Next:** P3 strategy dev\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 20:43 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] PM Balance Mystery: $57 in Unredeemed Positions\n\n**Task:** P1 copy intel \u2014 investigate growing PM balance discrepancy\n\n**Finding \u2014 $57.42 discrepancy TODAY, $80+ cumulative:**\n- Apr 3 trade math: +$34.15 P&L (4W/1L at ~$11.76/trade)\n- Expected balance: $929.12 | Actual CLOB: $871.70 | Gap: **$57.42**\n- W14 cumulative: balance dropped $952 \u2192 $871 (-$81) despite positive trade math\n\n**Root Cause: Bot never redeems winning PM positions.**\n- PM 5-min markets use CTF (Conditional Token Framework)\n- You buy YES shares \u2192 market resolves \u2192 winning shares are ERC-1155 tokens on Polygon\n- To convert back to USDC, shares must be \"merged\" or \"redeemed\" via smart contract\n- CLOB balance only shows free USDC, NOT unredeemed winning shares\n- The py_clob_client has NO merge/redeem methods\n- Bot has NO redemption code\n\n**Impact:** ~$57-80 of our capital is locked in unredeemed positions. This is NOT lost money \u2014 it's in our wallet as tokens, just needs to be converted back to USDC.\n\n**Fix Options:**\n1. **Manual:** Connect wallet to polymarket.com, positions page auto-redeems\n2.",
